==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Placet
<hw>Pla"cet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>placet</ets> it pleases.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A vote of assent,
as of the governing body of a university, of an ecclesiastical council,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The assent of the civil power to the promulgation of
an ecclesiastical ordinance.</def> <rj><au>Shipley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The king . . . annulled the royal <qex>placet</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>J. P. Peters.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Placid</ent>⟦br⟧
